pageContext.claim: “And China is not open. But we're open to them. They charge us 25, 35, 55 percent for things, and we charge them nothing in terms of coming into the country. Cars, they're at 25 percent, and we're at 2 percent and 2.5 percent.”
pageContext.analysis: This is a strange claim for Trump to make after imposing $250 billion worth of tariffs on China. In any case, China has a {15 percent} tariff on cars as of July 1, down from 25 percent. General Motors sells more cars in China (3.9 million) than in the United States (3 million) and saw its China business grow 13 percent in 2016.
